                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3294/29.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">McCormick</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Root informs Mr. McCormick that the consul at Marseilles telegraphed that
                    the imprisonment of Mr. Jacobs still continues, although the extradition was
                    authorized March 30. Mr. Root instructs Mr. McCormick to ascertain if the
                    continued detention is in accordance with the French law.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
